      "hypothesis": "ATR-scaled CUSUM bursts in the quiet bull regime mark discrete information arrival that is only partially impounded at the crossing; the burst direction (predominantly long, with the regime drift) continues over the following bars. Continuation is conditional on exogenous calm: flat 5-day VIX change and tight 21-day credit spreads. Bursts firing alongside rising VIX or widening credit are hedging-flow artifacts that revert and should be rejected by the meta-learner.",
      "causal_story": "Underreaction under low realized vol: in quiet bull phases repricing urgency is low and vol-targeted books are fully sized, so news diffuses slowly; a CUSUM crossing flags cumulative drift exceeding noise and the unimpounded remainder pays as continuation. Load-bearing discriminators are exogenous, not price transforms: cs_spread_21 (lower-ranked in this regime; within-regime widening marks stress-driven bursts that revert), vix_chg_5 (separates information bursts from hedging flow), real_yield_5y_z252d (higher-ranked; rising discount rates cap continuation). Volume only confirms participation. Primary stays single-condition at the dossier-measured default (803 in-regime events, 1.34x the 599 floor); all filtering is delegated to the meta.",
      "primary": "cusum_filter",
      "primary_params": {
        "threshold_atr": 1.0
      },
